Certainly! To generate a comprehensive list of all the countries in North America along with their population sizes and primary languages, you can create a JavaScript array of objects. Each object will represent a country, containing its name, population, and primary language(s). Below is a sample JavaScript code snippet that includes all the countries in North America:

```javascript
const northAmericanCountries = [
  { country: "Canada", population: 37590000, languages: ["English", "French"] },
  { country: "Mexico", population: 128932753, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "United States", population: 328200000, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Guatemala", population: 18209000, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Haiti", population: 11402533, languages: ["Haitian Creole", "French"] },
  { country: "Cuba", population: 11326616, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Dominican Republic", population: 10847904, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Honduras", population: 9904608, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Nicaragua", population: 6624554, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "El Salvador", population: 6486201, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Costa Rica", population: 5094118, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Panama", population: 4314768, languages: ["Spanish"] },
  { country: "Jamaica", population: 2961167, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Trinidad and Tobago", population: 1399488, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Belize", population: 397621, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Barbados", population: 287371, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Saint Lucia", population: 183627, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Grenada", population: 112003, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Saint Vincent and the Grenadines", population: 110940, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Antigua and Barbuda", population: 97928, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Saint Kitts and Nevis", population: 52823, languages: ["English"] },
  { country: "Bahamas", population: 385340, languages: ["English"] },
];

// Function to display the data
function displayCountriesInfo(countries) {
  countries.forEach((country) => {
    console.log(`Country: ${country.country}`);
    console.log(`Population: ${country.population}`);
    console.log(`Languages: ${country.languages.join(', ')}`);
    console.log('--------------------------');
  });
}

// Call the function to display the information
displayCountriesInfo(northAmericanCountries);
```

This script creates an array of objects `northAmericanCountries`, where each object contains the country's name, population, and an array of primary languages spoken. The `displayCountriesInfo` function iterates over each country object and logs the details to the console. You can execute this script in a JavaScript environment to see the list of countries along with their population sizes and primary languages.
